slide:
Covariant Return Types

Covariant Returns and Contravariant Parameters — Levi Morrison
https://wiki.php.net/rfc/covariant-returns-and-contravariant-parameters —

typed properties are invariant


<?php
class 🍞 {}
class 🥖 extends 🍞 {}

class Bakery
{
	public function gimme(): 🥖 {}
}

class Patisserie extends Bakery
{
	public function gimme(): 🍞 {}
}
?>


Fatal error: Declaration of Patisserie::gimme(): 🍞 must be compatible with Bakery::gimme(): 🥖

Return types are *co-variant*:
~they can *not* return a more broad type~
